  <chapter>
    <title>Same GNOME player's guide</title>

    <sect1 id="objective">
      <title>Game objective</title>
      <para>The objective of the game is to get a high score by
      eliminating as many balls as possible in a single stroke.  If
      you eliminate only two balls, you will score zero points.  If
      you eliminate three balls, you will score one point. The more
      balls you eliminate in a single mouse click the higher your
      score will be.</para>

      <para>To faciliate the task of spotting the ball clusters, Same
      GNOME will animate the cluster of balls when the mouse is over
      them (this also indicates that if you click on the cluster, it
      will eliminate the balls)</para>

      <para>Eliminating all of the balls on the board will grant you
      an extra one thousand points</para>
    </sect1>

