    <sect1 id="Authors">
      <title>Authors and history.</title>

      <para> This GNOME game was originally implemented by Miguel de
      Icaza and Federico Mena at early days of the GNOME project.  It
      was inspired by KDE's samegnome game which in turn was inspired
      by a Macintosh game of a similar name.</para>
      
      <para>A number of tiles were originated from the KDE
      project. The planets tile was rendered by Federico in his
      copious spare time to show the world his masterful control of
      povray command language.</para>

    </sect1>

  </chapter>

  <chapter id="newthemes">
    <title>Making new themes for Same GNOME</title>
      <para>Making new animation themes for Same GNOME is very simple.
      Each tile should measure forty by forty pixels.  You need to
      provide a graphic image that contains at least 3 rows of 40
      pixels each (for the three different tile colors) and a variable
      number of frames to do your animation (this animation will be
      shown when the mouse cursor is over a cluster of tiles of the
      same color).</para>

      <para>To allow Same-GNOME to pick up your tile set you need to
      install this on the $prefix/pixmaps/same-gnome directory (where
      $prefix stands for the installation prefix used to configure the
      GNOME environment, you can find this out by running the command
      <symbol>gnome-config --prefix</symbol>).</para>

  </chapter>
